'''Camaldolese Bible''' ({{lang-sk|Kamaldulská Biblia}}) is the first known complete transaltion of [[Bible]] into [[Slovak language]].<ref name="dorula">{{cite book |editor-first=Ján |editor-last=Doruľa |first=Ján |last=Doruľa |title= O prekladoch Biblie do slovenčiny a iných slovanských jazykov |chapter = Jazyková situácia na Slovensku v čase vzniku kamaldulského prekladu Biblie |p=10 | publisher=Slavistický kabinet SAV |location=Bratislava |year=1997 |isbn=80-967722-0-1 |language=Slovak}}</ref> The Bible was translated from [[Vulgate]] by [[Camaldolese]] monks at [[Červený Kláštor]] monastery. The completed translation had been rewrittten in 1756-1759.<ref name="dorula"/> The translation is characterized by the effort to use forms and expressions of common Slovak spoken language, with distinctive Western-Slovak elements and some literary linguistic elements of Czech origin.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slavu.sav.sk/fotografie/biblia.php |title=Kamaldulská Biblial |publisher=Jan Stanislav Institute of Slavistics of the Slovak Academy of Sciences |language=Slovak |access-date=14 November 2018}}</ref>
